        public ProtocolState(ServiceMessage parser)

      • ProtocolState

        public ProtocolState(ProtocolState.ProtocolType protocolType,
                     ServiceMessage parser)
        A Protocol State object maintains the state for a specific protocol running on the backup system. It keeps the relevant info needed for each protocol and is initiated by calling specific functions that handle each protocol type.
        Parameters:
        protocolType - the protocol type

    • Method Detail

      • initBackupState

        public boolean initBackupState(java.lang.String protocolVersion,
                               java.lang.String filepath,
                               int desiredRepDeg)
                        throws java.security.NoSuchAlgorithmException,
                               java.io.IOException
        Initialises the protocol state object for a backup procedure, calculates the total number of chunks of the file and the SHA256 hash of the filename and metadata. Returns whether initialisation was successful.
        Parameters:
        protocolVersion - the backup system version
        filepath - file path of the file to backup
        desiredRepDeg - desired replication degree
        Returns:
        whether initialisation was successful.
        Throws:
        java.security.NoSuchAlgorithmException
        java.io.IOException

      • computeSHA256

        private java.lang.String computeSHA256(java.lang.String filepath)
                                throws java.io.IOException,
                                       java.security.NoSuchAlgorithmException
        Computes a SHA256 hash based on the specified file path. The function uses the file's filename, last modified date and last accessed date to add more uniqueness to the hash.
        Parameters:
        filepath - the file path to use as base for the hash
        Returns:
        textual representation of the hexadecimal values of the SHA256
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
        java.security.NoSuchAlgorithmException
